---
import Book from "../layouts/Book.astro";
import ChapterOpener from "../components/ChapterOpener.astro";
---

<Book title="Colophon" description="How this site was made.">
  <ChapterOpener num="·" word="Colophon" subtitle="A note on how this book was set." />

  <section class="wrap">
    <p>
      This site is a printed book in browser form. The text was set in
      Instrument Serif (italic, for display), Inter Tight (for body), and
      JetBrains Mono (for code and operators). The drench is oklch(0.74 0.165
      62), a saffron that the design team chose against the prevailing
      navy-and-teal of developer-tool websites.
    </p>
    <p>
      The site is built with Astro and deployed on Cloudflare Pages.
      JavaScript is loaded only where it earns its place: the pipe-prompt
      bar, the type-in animation on the home page, and the lexicon-builder
      script that runs once at build time. Everything else is HTML and CSS.
    </p>
    <p>
      Every example pipe expression on this site is a real one. The lexicon
      is generated from the commands directory in the
      <a href="https://github.com/lunaos/luna-agents">luna-agents</a> repository
      at build time; the count you see in the masthead is the count at the
      most recent build.
    </p>
    <p>
      <small>
        Set on a Sunday afternoon, on a 16-inch laptop, in a cafe with the
        windows open.
      </small>
    </p>
  </section>
</Book>

<style>
  section { padding: var(--t-6) 0 var(--t-12); }
  p { max-width: var(--measure); }
</style>
